When I create, read, update, delete any file|folder with symbols that are escaped (' or any Cyrillic char ) - I got an error.

I've fixed it for me, patching WebdavServlet.java method getRelativePath(). On each return I unescape symbols:

protected String getRelativePath(HttpServletRequest request) {
		// Are we being processed by a RequestDispatcher.include()?
		if (request.getAttribute(Globals.INCLUDE_REQUEST_URI_ATTR) != null) {
			String result = (String) request
					.getAttribute(Globals.INCLUDE_PATH_INFO_ATTR);
			if ((result == null) || (result.equals("")))
				result = "/";
			return unescape(result);
		}

		// No, extract the desired path directly from the request
		String result = request.getPathInfo();
		if ((result == null) || (result.equals(""))) {
			result = "/";
		}
		return unescape(result);
	}

This unescape() method is from official W3C site:
http://www.w3.org/International/unescape.java

Now it works excellent for me.
